## Architecture

This project follows **hexagonal architecture** (ports & adapters):

```
cmd/                    # Application entry points
config/                 # Configuration loading
domain/                 # Domain types, errors, value objects
port/                   # Inbound & outbound port interfaces
service/                # Business logic (depends on ports)
adapter/                # Concrete implementations
  httphandler/          # HTTP transport (Chi)
{{- if .HasGRPC}}
  grpchandler/          # gRPC transport
{{- end}}
{{- if .HasKafka}}
  kafkahandler/         # Kafka consumer
{{- end}}
{{- if .HasMySQL}}
  mysqlrepo/            # MySQL repositories
{{- end}}
{{- if .HasRedis}}
  redisrepo/            # Redis repositories
{{- end}}
{{- if .HasEmail}}
  emailgateway/         # Email sending
{{- end}}
platform/               # Cross-cutting concerns
  lifecycle/            # Application lifecycle management
  observability/        # Logging, tracing, metrics
  httpclient/           # Resilient HTTP client
internal/testutil/      # Test helpers
```

## Getting Started

```bash
# Install dependencies
go mod tidy

# Run in development mode
make dev

# Build
make build

# Run tests
make test

# Lint
make lint
```

## Configuration

Copy the example config and adjust:

```bash
cp config/config.yaml.example config.yaml
```

Environment variables override config file values with the `APP_` prefix.

## Docker

```bash
# Start all services
docker-compose up -d

# Build the image
make docker-build
```
